        "10:00 AM — Old City gali walk. Start at Dashashwamedh and walk north through the galis (lanes). Kachouri Gali for deep-fried kachoris. Thatheri Bazaar for brass and copper utensils. Bengali Tola for Banarasi silk weaving workshops — many are open to visitors and watching the handloom work is fascinating. The galis are 2 metres wide in places — this is Varanasi as it has been for centuries.",
