        "8:00 AM — Sarnath Archaeological Museum (opens 9 AM). The original Ashoka Lion Capital column head — India's national emblem — is displayed here. It's made of polished Chunar sandstone and 2,300 years old. Also the famous Deer Park sculpture and finest examples of Gupta period Buddhist art. Entry ₹25. Spend 45–60 minutes.",
