        "3:00 PM — Mehrangarh Fort. One of India's finest forts, towering 125 m above the city. Entry ₹200 Indian, ₹600 foreign (includes audio guide in English — this one is genuinely worth using, narrated by the current Maharaja). Allow 2.5 hours. The museum inside is excellent — shields, howdahs, palanquins, royal cradles. The view of the blue city from the fort walls at sunset is unmissable.",
        "5:30 PM — Jaswant Thada. 500 m from the fort, this white marble royal cenotaph was built in 1899. The semi-translucent Makrana marble glows golden at sunset. Entry ₹30. 20 minutes.",
        "7:00 PM — Walk Sadar Market (Clock Tower bazaar). The heart of old Jodhpur — spice sellers, lac bangles, embroidered textiles, and the famous Jodhpur mirchi bada (a spiced chilli fritter, ₹15). Buy powdered local spices directly from the ground-floor stalls — saffron, kesar, and dry chilli blends are excellent value here.",
        "9:00 PM — Dinner at On the Rocks restaurant (near Umaid Bhawan). Order dal baati churma (₹400), ker sangri (desert bean curry, ₹350), and pyaaz kachori (₹80). The outdoor seating and live folk music make it Jodhpur's most atmospheric dinner option.",
