    intro: "The Spiti Valley is not a destination — it is a different world. At 3,800–4,500 m in the trans-Himalayan rain shadow zone of Himachal Pradesh, Spiti is a cold desert of barren brown mountains, ancient monasteries perched on impossible rock spurs, turquoise rivers, and skies so dark at night that the Milky Way is visible with the naked eye. The journey from Delhi to Kaza (Spiti's main town) is 785 km via Shimla, Kinnaur, and Nako — typically done over 2 days with an overnight halt at Reckong Peo or Nako. This guide covers the route, the season window (May–November only), what SUV you need, and how to prepare for high altitude travel.",
