        "10:30 AM — Kibber Village (21 km from Kaza, 4,205 m). One of the world's highest motorable villages. The flat-roofed mud-brick houses, terraced barley fields, and snow peaks behind are the defining image of Spiti. Walk the village lanes (30 minutes) and visit the small gompa.",
