        "4:30 PM — Nakki Lake. A small artificial lake at the centre of Mount Abu — boat hire (₹150 for 30 minutes), lakeside walk, and the famous Toad Rock (a boulder formation resembling a toad, overlooking the lake). The lake is pretty rather than spectacular, but the 1.5 km circumference walk is pleasant.",
        "6:00 PM — Sunset Point. 2 km from the lake — the most visited spot in Mount Abu. Sunset over the Aravalli plains is genuinely impressive — the plains stretch 200 km in every direction below, turning gold and red as the sun sets. Crowded but worth it.",
